{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is cross-module data handoff (three collectors -> aggregator -> summary input). A unit test of one function is too narrow, but real OS/network/subprocess is not required because deterministic source stubs can expose missing/overwritten fields. Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified by behavior text focusing on payload composition (not real transport conditions); Agentic is disqualified because this checks input to summarization, not model output quality.","test_description":"Wire collector modules with three in-process test doubles returning distinct sentinel values, run report assembly, and assert the exact summary-input payload contains all three source sections/keys with no source dropped.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is error-propagation/orchestration across modules: one fetch failure must map to section-level fallback while pipeline continues. In-process stubs can reproduce the failure mode (exception/timeout surrogate) and verify continuation semantics. Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified because real network outages are not required to validate fallback logic; Agentic is disqualified because behavior text requires deterministic fallback note/continue behavior, not quality of model judgment.","test_description":"Configure one source client stub to fail and two to succeed, run report generation, assert process does not abort, and assert output includes the failed section marked `data unavailable` while other sections remain populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on the model’s actual generated content (factual fidelity), which a stub would always hide. This is exactly LLM-output-quality validation, so Integration is insufficient. Rejected higher level: Workflow is disqualified because behavior text references a single summary-generation step, not multiple agentic decisions chained in sequence.","test_description":"Run the real summary model on representative datasets and score factual consistency against source key values (for example numeric/entity extraction checks), enforcing a pass-rate threshold across repeated runs to account for nondeterminism.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external interfaces (source APIs + email transport/inbox delivery). Mocking can hide protocol/auth/delivery-path failures; end-to-end delivery requires real HTTP/SMTP or equivalent real service endpoints. Rejected higher levels: Agentic is disqualified because this behavior is delivery pipeline correctness, not model decision quality; Workflow is disqualified because it does not specify multiple agentic decision stages.","test_description":"Execute the script as a real process in a test environment with reachable test instances of the three data sources and email service, then verify the configured mailbox receives the report message with expected structure/content sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This spans real failure handling across process runs: transport failure, filesystem persistence, and retry on later execution. Mock-only tests often miss cross-run/state-persistence and real I/O edge cases. Integration brake check: requires real filesystem/process boundary behavior (a=yes), so not Integration; no model-output dependency (b=no); no multi-agentic chain (c/d=no). Rejected higher levels: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because behavior text is delivery retry mechanics, not LLM decision quality.","test_description":"Run script once with email endpoint intentionally unreachable and verify a persisted local report artifact is created; run script again in a new process with email restored and verify previously saved report is retried and delivered, then persistence state is cleared/updated appropriately.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.81,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
